
[1]perfidious

   PERFID'IOUS, a. [L. perfidus; per and fidus, faithful. Per in this word
   signifies through, beyond, or by, aside.]

   1. Violating good faith or vows; false to trust or confidence reposed;
   treacherous; as a perfidious agent; a perfidious friend. [See Perfidy.]

   2. Proceeding from treachery, or consisting in breach of faith; as a
   perfidious act.

   3. Guilty of violated allegiance; as a perfidious citizen; a man
   perfidious to his country.
